],{"class":41,"line":956},[39,1307,255],{"class":49},[39,1309,1310],{"class":41,"line":961},[39,1311,105],{"class":49},[39,1313,1314,1316,1318,1320,1322,1324,1326,1328],{"class":41,"line":966},[39,1315,160],{"class":62},[39,1317,163],{"class":45},[39,1319,63],{"class":62},[39,1321,168],{"class":62},[39,1323,121],{"class":58},[39,1325,81],{"class":49},[39,1327,175],{"class":84},[39,1329,99],{"class":49},[39,1331,1332,1334,1336,1338],{"class":41,"line":985},[39,1333,183],{"class":49},[39,1335,59],{"class":58},[39,1337,629],{"class":49},[39,1339,632],{"class":363},[39,1341,1342,1344,1346,1348],{"class":41,"line":996},[39,1343,638],{"class":49},[39,1345,141],{"class":62},[39,1347,643],{"class":84},[39,1349,534],{"class":49},[39,1351,1352,1354,1356],{"class":41,"line":1007},[39,1353,183],{"class":49},[39,1355,59],{"class":58},[39,1357,188],{"class":49},[18,1359,1360],{},[192,1361],{"alt":486,"src":1362},"https:\u002F\u002Fi.imgur.com\u002Fd7qm9d6.png",[13,1364,1366],{"id":1365},"a-bonus-note-on-classes","A bonus note on classes",[18,1368,1369],{},"Thanks to Yu-Hsuan from a friend's blog who explained this concept using a game analogy. Here's how they put it:",[29,1371,1376],{"className":1372,"code":1374,"language":1375,"meta":34},[1373],"language-text","Prototype — I like to explain this with games.\n\nIn Ragnarok Online, the Novice class is basically the prototype of every other class.\nDoesn't matter if you're 1st job, 2nd job, 3rd job, transcendent 2nd job — they all inherit from Novice.\n\nSo Novice's skills (methods) are available to everyone.\n\nIf you're a Rune Knight, you can still use First Aid (an inherited method from Novice — Rune Knight itself doesn't have it, so when a Rune Knight casts it, the lookup goes Rune Knight → Lord Knight → Knight → Swordsman → Novice) — walking up the chain looking for the First Aid skill (method).\n","text",[36,1377,1374],{"__ignoreMap":34},[18,1379,1380],{},"This is a great hands-on example of prototype, prototype chain, and prototype inheritance. It's a much more intuitive way to wrap your head around the prototype concept.",[1382,1383,1384],"style",{},"html pre.shiki code .sCcAr, html code.shiki .sCcAr{--shiki-default:#91CBFF}html pre.shiki code .sMAXC, html code.shiki .sMAXC{--shiki-default:#F0F3F6}html pre.shiki code .sj_SG, html code.shiki .sj_SG{--shiki-default:#DBB7FF}html pre.shiki code .sWyjQ, html code.shiki .sWyjQ{--shiki-default:#FF9492}html pre.shiki code .sTRMh, html code.shiki .sTRMh{--shiki-default:#ADDCFF}html pre.shiki code .s_sBn, html code.shiki .s_sBn{--shiki-default:#FFB757}html .default .shiki span {color: var(--shiki-default);background: var(--shiki-default-bg);font-style: var(--shiki-default-font-style);font-weight: var(--shiki-default-font-weight);text-decoration: var(--shiki-default-text-decoration);}html .shiki span {color: var(--shiki-default);background: var(--shiki-default-bg);font-style: var(--shiki-default-font-style);font-weight: var(--shiki-default-font-weight);text-decoration: var(--shiki-default-text-decoration);}html pre.shiki code .sQrFR, html code.shiki .sQrFR{--shiki-default:#BDC4CC}",{"title":34,"searchDepth":72,"depth":72,"links":1386},[1387,1388,1389,1390],{"id":15,"depth":72,"text":16},{"id":23,"depth":72,"text":24},{"id":329,"depth":72,"text":330},{"id":1365,"depth":72,"text":1366},"TypeScript","2019-06-23 11:43:56","md","en",{},"\u002Fen\u002Ftypescript\u002Fts-fundamentals-classes","3",{"title":6,"description":20},false,"en\u002FTypeScript\u002Fts-fundamentals-classes",[1402,1403,1391],"TypeScript Fundamentals","JavaScript",null,"\u002Fen\u002Ftypescript\u002F2019\u002F06\u002F23\u002Fts-fundamentals-classes\u002F","zwCYL56kHQqCCFuW9r7vukjFZj-I1ucSEIEAu0y8XDk",{"newer":1408,"older":1412},{"url":1409,"title":1410,"date":1411},"\u002Fen\u002Fjavascript\u002F2019\u002F06\u002F24\u002Fjavascript-prototype-chain\u002F","Trying to Wrap My Head Around the JavaScript Prototype Chain","2019-06-24 12:28:48",{"url":1413,"title":1414,"date":1415},"\u002